rce":"recfc0WEkVsVeq91r","target":"recokV9koCd9sHkZo","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recLqdNqdfRBXIFKp","ref":"Matt.4.1","text":"Then was Jesus led up of the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted of the devil.","year":26},{"id":"recN80R83DVJNaGcd","ref":"Matt.4.2","text":"And when he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was afterward an hungred.","year":26},{"id":"recl7cTtGU9feN8iK","ref":"Matt.4.3","text":"And when the tempter came to him, he said, If thou be the Son of God, command that these stones be made bread.","year":26},{"id":"recdPykn1V8KLYmoB","ref":"Matt.4.4","text":"But he answered and said, It is written, Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God.","year":26},{"id":"reciFgaWpkZ0aV3K5","ref":"Matt.4.5","text":"Then the devil taketh him up into the holy city, and setteth him on a pinnacle of the temple,","year":26},{"id":"recNb2k6x6eq5nwoD","ref":"Matt.4.6","text":"And saith unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast thyself down: for it is written, He shall give his angels charge concerning thee: and in their hands they shall bear thee up, lest at any time thou dash thy foot against a stone.","year":26},{"id":"recJsSUm9KITTIuuu","ref":"Matt.4.7","text":"Jesus said unto him, It is written again, Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy God.","year":26},{"id":"recVcnwBskpJbfRyh","ref":"Matt.4.8","text":"Again, the devil taketh him up into an exceeding high mountain, and sheweth him all the kingdoms of the world, and the glory of them;","year":26}]}
